reviews.text: An historic station (formerly Aycliffe Lane) on the route of the Stockton and Darlington Railway, which opened in 1825. The 1827 agentʼs office and tavern, although no longer in use, are the oldest surviving buildings at any operational station in the county. However, due to the age and relative infrequency of trains plus the somewhat rudimentary nature of the waiting shelters, one might be forgiven for thinking that things havenʼt changed that much for the past two centuries.
